The '''An'yettu clan''' was a family of [[Rodian/Legends|Rodians]] on [[Rodia/Legends|Rodia]]. Locked in an endless feud with the [[Chattza clan/Legends|Chattza Clan]], the ancient tribe hailed from the [[An'yettu Islands/Legends|An'yettu Islands]], resolving to remain withdrawn from politics. [[Grand Protector/Legends|Grand Protector]] [[Navik/Legends|Navik the Red]] ensured the continuation of this isolation by preventing them from expanding beyond this archipelago.<ref>''[[Shadows of the Empire Planets Guide]]''</ref> 

[[Opdoa]] of the assignment committee of the [[Goa-Ato/Legends|Goa-Ato]], was surprised to hear that a member of that clan, [[Fask Eelak]], made it to become a [[bounty hunter/Legends|hunter]] of the Guild.<ref>{{WEGCite|story=New Assignments|book=Shadows of the Empire Planets Guide}}</ref>

{{Family-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The An'yettu clan was first mentioned in ''[[Shadows of the Empire Planets Guide]]''.

In [[Fantasy Flight Games]]' [[roleplaying game]] sourcebook ''[[Dangerous Covenants]]'', there is an adventure seed where the players join the Guardians of the clan in fighting off Chattza Clan raiders. The players can succeed in their mission, or fail and be forced to retreat.
